summary: Doctor Hawkins checks on Mr. Smith, who hasn't had a check-up in 5 years. He advises him to get one annually and to quit smoking for his health. Mr. Smith is a smoker and has tried to quit many times but hasn't succeeded.

Mrs. Parker and Dr. Peters discuss Ricky's vaccination schedule. Ricky is 14 months old and due for Hepatitis A, Chickenpox, and Measles shots. Dr. Peters can only give him these for now, and will administer the rest in a couple of weeks. Mrs. Parker may also need a Tetanus booster.
Person1 lost their keys and a small foot ornament. They asked Person2 for help, who agreed to assist them. After searching, Person2 found the items, and Person1 expressed their gratitude.

Person1 is upset that Person2 didn't tell them about their girlfriend and that they were in love. Person2 apologizes and says they thought Person1 knew. Person1 is frustrated that Person2 didn't think it mattered and that they were going to marry her.
Malik approaches Wen and Nikki, asking for a dance. Wen declines but allows Malik to dance with Nikki.
Lisa wishes Aims a happy birthday and gives her a present. Aims is excited about the gift and introduces her friends to Lisa.
Two people discuss a $10 fare for a ride. The driver explains the fare structure, which includes a base rate of $2 for the first 2 km and 20 cents for each additional 200 m.

Judy Liao, an applicant for the accounts assistant position, visited the company to confirm that her resume was received. She had sent her resume along with a cover letter, two letters of recommendation, as requested. The company confirmed they had received her application and did not require any additional documents.Person2 asks Person1 about the interview schedule for a job. Person1 is unsure but mentions that resumes are still being received and interviews might start after a week or two. Person2 thanks Person1 for their help and they exchange goodbyes.
Person1 describes a basic computer package with a good CPU, 256 MB of RAM, a built-in modem, and a 15-inch monitor. Person2 asks about a modem and monitor, and decides to buy the package.

Person1 asks Person2 to go to the store and buy a small bag of sugar, four oranges, and a half gallon of milk. Person2 agrees and confirms the quantities and amount of money needed.

Person1 and Person2 discuss Bean's inappropriate and harassing emails. They suggest using a spam filter to block unwanted content.

Keith is 21 years old and James is a year older. James looks younger than his age. Person1's father is fine and retired last week. He wants to travel the world in his retirement. Person2 agrees that having an active retirement is a good idea and plans to spend their old age similarly.

Person1 and Person2 discuss their music preferences. Person1 enjoys classical music for its relaxing and brain-stimulating effects, while Person2 prefers lively dance music for its energy. They both acknowledge some benefits of each genre, such as reducing stress and improving cognitive performance.Two people discuss the benefits of listening to classical music for increasing brain power and the influence of music on a person's feeling and character. They also suggest exploring different types of music to find what suits one's mood and preferences.

Person1 is confused about what Person2 said and is unsure if Person2 wants to help or scold them. Person2 suggests that Person1 should consider the situation and believes that Person2's intentions are good.

Person1 compliments Person2's triplets, noting their resemblance to their parents and asking about plans for more children. Person2 expresses exhaustion and frustration with sleepless nights, but acknowledges that the labor and delivery went smoothly. Person1 offers encouragement, reminding Person2 that the challenges will be worth it in the long run.

Person1 and Person2 discuss their favorite ice cream flavors, with both preferring chocolate. They dislike ice cream with nuts and agree that garlic ice cream is disgusting. They decide to stick with regular ice cream choices.
Person1 invites Person2 to work with them, and they agree to join. Person2 is excited and eager to start.

The speakers discuss their flight check-in process, including ID checks, luggage, and potential security measures. They have 30 minutes before take-off and are aware of the security concerns.

Person1 calls the moving company and asks for a quote to move from the 8th floor to the 6th floor, a distance of 15 kilometers. The moving company explains that the cost depends on the floor, distance, and furniture. Person1 wants to pay the full amount in advance, but the moving company explains that they only pay 50% in advance and the rest after the move is completed. Person1 also asks about the damage and compensation clause.Damaged articles can be claimed for compensation.

Person1 and Person2 discuss their favorite movie, Superbad. They both find it hilarious and agree to watch it together at Person1's place.

Person1 visits a bar for the first time and is curious about the security check. Person2 explains it's just a precaution and mentions it's common in China too. Person1 enjoys the decoration and Person2 recommends getting a free drink with a ticket. Person1 chooses orange juice and is concerned about getting a drink due to the crowd.Person2 explains how they can get the bartender's attention and that the bartenders know whose turn it is.

A person asks a stranger for help to get to Central Park. The stranger assists the person by calling out the bus stops and ensuring they get off at the correct stop. The person thanks the stranger for their help.

Mr. White expresses disappointment and offers a raise, but Jessica declines, stating that the new job aligns with her interests. Mr. White wishes her good luck and offers to write a letter of recommendation if needed.

They chose Person1's company because of the potential for personal development and their connections in the Northeast region.

They haven't considered looking for magazines or newspaper articles.Person1 suggests using the Reader's Guide to Periodical Literature to find magazine articles. Person2 plans to start with books and then move on to magazines. Person1 offers help at the Reference Desk.

They took a boat tour on the Seine River and visited art museums, but found them boring. They spent a lot of time in cafes, enjoying French coffee and watching people. Person1 wishes they could have a vacation like that someday.

They also rule out the Grand Theater and the Center due to their preferences. They ultimately decide not to go downtown, as they don't want to spend a lot of money.Two people discuss a baseball game on TV tonight featuring New York and Boston. Person 1 wishes to study abroad but thought it required knowing a foreign language. Lisa informs Person 1 that there are programs that don't require this.

Sue enjoyed her holiday in the country with friends, camping in the mountains near Snowdon. They had good weather, met friendly people, and cooked over an open fire. They returned early this morning, tired from their journey. Person 1 stayed at home and had a less exciting weekend.

Person1 is upset that Person2 didn't tell them about their girlfriend and that they were in love. Person2 apologizes and explains they didn't think it was important. Person1 is frustrated and feels betrayed.

Person2 has three years of work experience and wants to do a management job. They plan to apply their specialty and experience to their role and eventually move up to a management position in the company.

Person2 suggests the possibility of changing the terms in the future if their relationship continues to grow.

Person1 and Person2 discuss their preferences for living in a mountain village or a big town. Person2 enjoys the fresh air and charm of the mountain village, while Person1 prefers the lively atmosphere of a big town. They both agree on the charm of walking along the hill.

Jenny and Person1 are at a party. Jenny is having a good time and enjoys the food and people. Person1 is a great host and offers Jenny more champagne.

Person1 is considering taking a class with Dr. Miller next semester, but is worried about grades. Person2 shares their positive experience with Dr. Miller's class and mentions his background in the military. Person2 encourages Person1 to make the best decision for themselves.

Richard praises it as a fine film with an enchanting story, while David criticizes it for lacking originality and being predictable.Two people discuss the movie "The Lion King". The conversation ends with a tease for their next movie discussion.

Person1 suggests hiring someone to help with the housework, but Person2 is hesitant due to his concern for his elderly mother. Person2 suggests going to see Citizen Kane and leaves to go swimming. They agree to go swimming tomorrow, but Person1 might have to work at the studio. They say their goodbyes and end the conversation.
The new baby is sleeping better since #Person2's mother moved in, but #Person2 is still kept awake by her thoughts as a mother.

Person2 agrees to avoid getting close to babies if they smoke, and Person1 suggests that smoking parents should either avoid getting close to babies or quit smoking altogether.
